description.plain:
“I write songs to make people feel things.  All life experiences, no matter their magnitude, hum with their own beautiful tone which I feel the urge and obligation to channel into song.

I have been singing, playing and reading music since I was nine, but it wasn’t until my high school semester abroad that I began creating original content. Being a song-leader on the program, I saw that I was capable of inducing emotion with music. I wanted those emotions to be authentic.

Returning to Los Angeles, I joined Music Technology and Music Theory classes, digging through musical software to embody the software of my thoughts. I made new friends who educated me across all fields, from production and engineering to video storyboarding and directing. I am learning and loving the fact that musical creativity is boundless, and technology helps expand the reach.

Thank you for listening to my music and embracing my visions. Your support is the engine of my creativity."


-Kinneret’s website
https://www.kinneret.org/biography/

songs.title: No Wind Resistance!

description.plain:
“No Wind Resistance!”, Kinneret’s most popular song by a wide margin also carries her most notable quirks. Powerful metaphor and unique sound make it memorable beyond the norm.
  The song became popular on the famous social media app, TikTok in 2019 and 2020. A slight synth beat in the background with bass.
